description:
Currently tk run output goes through multiple disconnected paths:
1. fmt.Printf in run.go — terminal only
2. slog in generator/engine — stderr only
3. SSE events from board server — board only (reconstructed from file watchers)
4. [DEBUG] lines — board server stderr only

The board live panel misses progress output visible in the terminal, and vice versa. Create a RunOutput module that all status updates flow through, routing to terminal, board SSE, cloud sync, and run logs from a single source of truth.

Interface sketch:
  type RunOutput struct { ... }
  func (o *RunOutput) Status(msg string, fields ...any)
  func (o *RunOutput) TaskStarted(taskID, title string)
  func (o *RunOutput) TaskCompleted(taskID string, result IterationResult)
  func (o *RunOutput) ContextProgress(elapsed time.Duration, tokens int)
  func (o *RunOutput) WaveStarted(wave int, taskCount int)
  etc.

Files: new internal/output/ package, then refactor run.go and engine callbacks to use it.
